Background:
We have a fairly small team who is new to Swerve and are struggling on the code side. We have one student who knows Java and while I know Java, I have no experience with getting this going and am hoping YAGSL would help us bridge the gap. Students fundraised in the Spring for a Swerve config using WCP Swerve X Flipped, Krakens + Neos, Cancoders and a Pigeon 2 which is what we now have and are trying to code. Unfortunately didn’t raise enough for the second set of krakens to use the out of box CTRE configurator.

As we try to get our basic starter robot code deployed to the robot, we get an IllegalStateException error on com.revrobotics.spark.SparkBase.configure which is called from our SwerveSubsystem when instantiating a SwerveDrive. We’ve tried to instantiate this SwerveDrive in simpler ways but it always seems to error out.

Our code is here. It doesn’t do anything yet really…we are just getting started and its been a stumble. Any help is appreciated.
